criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Ischemic or hemorrhagic stroke, diagnosed clinically and by imagery, more than one
             month after onset;

          -  Severe upper limb paresis with Upper-Extremity Fugl-Meyer Score < 19/60 .

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Significant limitation in upper limb function predating the recent stroke, caused by
             former symptomatic stroke and/or an orthopedic/rheumatologic disease;

          -  Neuropsychologic or psychiatric impairment with significant interference with
             participation in therapy;

          -  Severe visual impairment.
